A plastic deep plate is a type of dish that is made from plastic material and has a deeper and larger design compared to regular plates.
It is commonly used for serving meals that contain sauces, gravies, or liquids that need to be contained within the plate.

  • Material: Plastic deep plates are typically made from durable and food-grade plastic materials such as polypropylene or polystyrene. These materials are lightweight, easy to clean, and resistant to breakage.
  • Size and shape: Plastic deep plates come in various sizes and shapes.
    They are deeper than regular plates, with higher sides to prevent spills and keep the food contained within the plate.
    The larger size also allows for serving generous portions of food.
  • Versatility: Plastic deep plates are versatile and can be used for a wide range of meals, including soups, stews, pasta dishes, salads, or any meal that requires containing liquids or saucy components.
    They are commonly used in parties, picnics, outdoor events, and catering services.
  • Convenience: Plastic deep plates are lightweight and stackable, making them easy to store and transport.
    They are also disposable, which means they can be discarded after use, saving time and effort on cleaning.
